author: Chris Morgan
commit_message:
add NVD3Chart.buildcontent()

NVD3Chart().buildcontent() constructs NVD3Chart().htmlcontent with no head,
body tags. To be useful probably need the attribute jquery_on_ready to be set,
so the chart is evaluated once the page is loaded.

This is useful if you are plugging NVD3Chart into another templating engine
(such as Tornado's) and simply require the chart and content.

Note: updated examples/demo_all.py to use the buildcontent() method.

commit_message:
Allow easier customizing of the y-axis formats

This is especially useful if you have a line
and bar chart with two data series with extreme differences.
Such as:

    data_y1 = [10, 13, 14, 20]
    data_y2 = [0.0003, 0.0032, 0.0057, 0.0081]

In the above case one may one would like to format the first
y axis with:

        cart.y1Axis
                    .tickFormat(d3.format(',f'));

and the second y axis with:

        chart.y2Axis
                    .tickFormat(function(d) {
                     return d3.format(',0.4f')(d) });

This is now possible with passing a keyword ```yaxis2_format```
when creating a new ```linePlusBarChart`:

    chart = linePlusBarChart(name="linePlusBarChart",
                             width=500, height=400, x_axis_format=None,
                             yaxis2_format="function(d) { return d3.format(',0.4f')(d) }")

commit_message:
Add a new class DiscreteBarChart

Note the capital D. This is a new class which does not
render so many templates like discreteBarChart. Rather,
this class renders a templates which exploits Jinja
template inheritance. This template simply extends the template
content.html.

Future release can do:

    discreteBarChart = DiscreteBarChart

Such that, if discreteBarChart is removed the old class is still
available from the user's point of view.

Also, this class violates the DRY principle, it overrides methods
of NVD3Chart base class. This pattern will be introduced by all
other Capital letter new classes. This methods can be moved later to
a Mixin class.
